# ── Project structure ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# accident_detection/
# ├── 01_prepare_data.py      Load datasets, segment windows, normalize
# ├── 02_augment.py           Physics-preserving data augmentation
# ├── 03_train.py             Train 1D-CNN, save best model
# ├── 04_evaluate_export.py   Evaluate + export TFLite int8 + C header
# ├── requirements.txt        This file
# ├── data/
# │   ├── raw/
# │   │   ├── boubezoul/      Boubezoul 2019 PTW dataset CSVs
# │   │   └── normal_riding/  Normal riding / road IMU CSVs
# │   └── processed/          Generated by 01_prepare_data.py
# ├── models/
# │   ├── best_model.keras    Saved Keras model
# │   ├── model_int8.tflite   Quantized model → deploy to ESP32
# │   ├── model_int8.h        C header → copy into Arduino sketch folder
# │   └── training_curves.png
# └── accident_detector/
#     └── accident_detector.ino   Arduino/ESP32 firmware
#
# ── Run order ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   python 01_prepare_data.py
#   python 02_augment.py
#   python 03_train.py
#   python 04_evaluate_export.py
#
#   Then copy models/model_int8.h into accident_detector/
#   Open accident_detector.ino in Arduino IDE and flash to ESP32
#
# ── Expected performance targets ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   Recall (accident detection rate):  > 95%
#   False alarm rate:                  < 5%
#   Inference time on ESP32:           < 50ms per window
#   Model size (int8):                 < 200 KB
